Component.Description: This library calculates the brake build up times and the other time variables applied in the formulas of speed and distance monitoring.

Module.Description: This library calculates the brake build up times and the other time variables applied in the formulas of speed and distance monitoring.

Method.Description: This function calculates the safe brake build up time T_be.

Output.Remark: Time_Set->T_be is assigned a value. The other fields of Time_Set are irrelevant.

Interface.Precondition:
```math 0 \leq M\_NVKTINT \leq 31, and M\_NVKTINT \in N ``` Is_Conversion_Model_Applicable is either TRUE or FALSE.
```math 0 \leq Traction\_Model->T\_brake\_emergency \leq 205, and Traction\_Model->T\_brake\_emergency \in R ``` The other fields of Traction_Model are irrelevant.
Remark: The unit of Traction_Model->T_brake_emergency is Second.
Interface.Postcondition:
```math 0 \leq Time\_Set->T\_be \leq 320, and Time\_Set->T\_be \in R ```
Remark: The unit of Time_Set->T_be is Second. The other fields of Time_Set are irrelevant.

Method.Processing:
Time_Set->T_be is set:
Time_Set->T_be = Traction_Model->T_brake_emergency
The condition (TRUE == Is_Conversion_Model_Applicable) is checked, * if TRUE, Kt_int is set:
Kt_int = M_NVKTINT * M_NVKTINT_RESOLUTION
Time_Set->T_be is set:
Time_Set->T_be = Kt_int * (Traction_Model->T_brake_emergency) * if FALSE, no operation

Component.Remark: Implementation of service brake feedback is not considered at the moment.
